"Change Set:		9412Deprecated-nice.2311Deprecated-nice.2:deprecate Number class>>#readExactlyFrom:#readFrom: now does the same job.This was just an interim message for smooth transition introduced in 3.9. Anyway, who would request a readInexactly feature?"!!Number class methodsFor: '*311Deprecated' stamp: 'nice 2/22/2010 22:41'!readExactlyFrom: stringOrStream 	"Answer a number as described on aStream. The number may	include a leading radix specification, as in 16rFADE"		self deprecated: 'Use #readFrom: '.	^ self readFrom: stringOrStream ! !